goes like the slappers.

94
00:06:32,350 --> 00:06:34,588
Nothing to be worried about.
Does it before every race.

95
00:06:34,590 --> 00:06:37,228
Good sign, actually.
Means he's stoked.

96
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:39,928
All Formula 3 cars to
the assembly area.

97
00:06:39,930 --> 00:06:41,329
Now, please.

98
00:06:52,240 --> 00:06:55,470
...drivers please bring them
to the scrutineering bay now.

99
00:06:56,110 --> 00:06:58,009
All right, Superstar?

100
00:06:58,009 --> 00:06:59,579
Never better, patron.

101
00:06:59,579 --> 00:07:02,050
- Have a gargle with this.
- Thank you.

102
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:06,088
Quick toke of this.

103
00:07:06,089 --> 00:07:09,389
At Crystal Palace today,
James Hunt's on pole,

104
00:07:09,389 --> 00:07:12,959
with Austrian newcomer
Niki Lauda alongside him

105
00:07:12,959 --> 00:07:15,699
and Dave Walker
completing Row 1.

106
00:07:15,699 --> 00:07:18,629
Row 2 is Mike Beuttler
and Dave Morgan,

107
00:07:18,629 --> 00:07:20,399
with Tony Trimmer
and Gerry Birrell.

108
00:07:20,399 --> 00:07:21,538
Who's that?

109
00:07:21,540 --> 00:07:22,589
He's new.

110
00:07:23,399 --> 00:07:26,129
- Some German.
- Austrian.

111
00:07:26,439 --> 00:07:29,408
He's been here since 5 a.m.
walking the track.

112
00:07:29,410 --> 00:07:32,149
You might actually have to
concentrate today, James.

113
00:07:32,149 --> 00:07:33,879
You'll need these.

114
00:07:34,250 --> 00:07:36,220
Okay, start her up.

115
00:07:36,620 --> 00:07:39,230
Ah! What music!

116
00:07:39,319 --> 00:07:41,259
They could never
have imagined it,

117
00:07:41,259 --> 00:07:43,689
those pioneers who
invented the automobile,

118
00:07:43,689 --> 00:07:45,658
that it would possess
us like this,

119
00:07:45,659 --> 00:07:48,228
in our imaginations, our dreams.

120
00:07:48,230 --> 00:07:50,728
Nursie, men love women,

121
00:07:50,730 --> 00:07:52,699
but even more than that,

122
00:07:52,699 --> 00:07:55,290
