123
00:08:03,180 --> 00:08:06,410
- Come on, James!
- It's James! Go on, James!

124
00:08:07,350 --> 00:08:08,649
Go, James!

125
00:08:16,290 --> 00:08:17,528
<i>Hunt's still in the lead,</i>

126
00:08:17,529 --> 00:08:20,220
<i>but Niki Lauda is
right on his tail!</i>

127
00:08:28,470 --> 00:08:31,538
<i>Hunt and Lauda are proving to
be in a class of their own.</i>

128
00:08:31,540 --> 00:08:33,668
<i>They're leaving the
pack far behind.</i>

129
00:08:33,669 --> 00:08:36,230
Herr Red Devil's on his tail.

130
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:43,450
<i>Lauda takes a look
down the inside...</i>

131
00:08:44,620 --> 00:08:47,210
<i>...and he's sold him a dummy!</i>

132
00:08:50,090 --> 00:08:52,629
<i>Lauda is through!
He's in the lead!</i>

133
00:08:52,629 --> 00:08:56,080
<i>Hunt will be determined to
make up for that mistake.</i>

134
00:09:01,970 --> 00:09:03,668
<i>Hunt's in Lauda's slipstream.</i>

135
00:09:03,669 --> 00:09:06,269
<i>Lauda's not leaving any gap.</i>

136
00:09:11,009 --> 00:09:12,609
<i>The Lotus goes for the inside.</i>

137
00:09:12,610 --> 00:09:14,909
<i>It's an aggressive
move from Hunt.</i>

138
00:09:19,289 --> 00:09:20,879
<i>There's contact!</i>

139
00:09:27,429 --> 00:09:31,269
<i>The leaders have spun out!
Lauda's facing the wrong way!</i>

140
00:09:31,269 --> 00:09:33,529
<i>The back marker's gone through!</i>

141
00:09:34,139 --> 00:09:36,239
<i>You can see why Hunter's
fellow drivers call him.</i>

142
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:37,970
<i>"Hunt the Shunt."</i>

143
00:09:41,409 --> 00:09:42,408
Asshole!

144
00:09:42,409 --> 00:09:44,349
- Go on, James!
- The Kraut's out of it!

145
00:09:44,350 --> 00:09:46,278
<i>Lauda is clearly furious.</i>

146
00:09:46,279 --> 00:09:49,479
<i>There's every reason to expect
sharp words in the pit.</i>

147
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:51,719
<i>It's going to be
victory for Hunt.</i>

148
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:55,210
<i>It's going to be an ignominious
defeat for Niki Lauda.</i>

149
00:09:59,559 --> 00:10:03,058
<i>So James Hunt scores his
third major Formula 3 win</i>

150
00:10:03,059 --> 00:10:05,198
<i>of the season here,
at Crystal Palace,</i>

151
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:08,038
<i>after a desperate
battle with Niki Lauda.</i>

152
00:10:08,039 --> 00:10:10,038
<i>Lauda was unable so restart</i>

153
00:10:10,039 --> 00:10:12,938
<i>after Hunt's aggressive move
caused them both to spin out</i>

154
00:10:12,940 --> 00:10:15,239
<i>in the last lap of the race.</i>

155
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:17,078
Hard luck. Better
luck next time.

156
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:18,200
Hey, asshole!

157
00:10:20,009 --> 00:10:22,379
That was my line. I
had that corner.

158
00:10:22,379 --> 00:10:24,149
You mean the one
that you spun out of

159
00:10:24,149 --> 00:10:25,989
and finished facing
the other way?

160
00:10:25,990 --> 00:10:27,759
I think that corner had you.

161
00:10:27,759 --> 00:10:30,489
That move was total suicide.
What if I hadn't braked?

162
00:10:30,490 --> 00:10:33,229
- We'd have crashed.
- But we didn't, did we?

163
00:10:33,230 --> 00:10:36,460
Thanks to your impeccable
survival instincts.

164
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:39,730
Fuck you! What's your name?

165
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,399
James Simon Wallis Hunt.

166
00:10:43,769 --> 00:10:46,038
Remember it, my
little Jerry friend.

167
00:10:46,039 --> 00:10:49,139
- Jawohl! Remember ze name.
- It's very simple.

168
00:10:49,139 --> 00:10:51,479
Hunt, it rhymes with cunt!

169
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:54,740
A word that happens to
describe you perfectly.

170
00:10:55,220 --> 00:10:56,349
Who was that?

171
00:10:56,350 --> 00:10:59,649
I've no idea. He looks
like a rat, doesn't he?

172
00:11:01,220 --> 00:11:02,719
<i>In my hometown, Vienna,</i>

173
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:05,028
<i>my family's famous
for one thing:</i>

174
00:11:05,029 --> 00:11:06,149
<i>Business.</i>

175
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:09,158
<i>My grandfather was
a businessman,</i>

176
00:11:09,159 --> 00:11:10,720
<i>my father, too.</i>

177
00:11:11,330 --> 00:11:14,629
<i>So when they heard I wanted
to race cars for a living,</i>

178
00:11:14,629 --> 00:11:16,500
<i>They are a few things to say.</i>

179
00:11:41,399 --> 00:11:42,360
Good.

180
00:12:03,379 --> 00:12:06,019
<i>So if my family wasn't
going to help me,</i>

181
00:12:06,019 --> 00:12:09,558
<i>I decided to risk everything
and take out a Loan myself.</i>

182
00:12:09,559 --> 00:12:12,489
<i>I found a Formula 1
team with an Ok car</i>

183
00:12:12,490 --> 00:12:14,798
<i>and an owner who had
run out of money</i>

184
00:12:14,799 --> 00:12:17,129
<i>and was willing to
accept my terms.</i>

185
00:12:17,129 --> 00:12:19,168
And so, ladies and gentlemen,

186
00:12:19,169 --> 00:12:20,969
I'm delighted to say...

187
00:12:20,970 --> 00:12:23,639
that the winner of the Guild
of Motoring Writers Award.

188
00:12:23,639 --> 00:12:25,938
Driver of the Year...

189
00:12:25,940 --> 00:12:27,340
is James Hunt.

190
00:12:30,580 --> 00:12:32,070
Superb news!

191
00:12:33,009 --> 00:12:35,110
- Well done, James.
- Superstar!

192
00:12:35,519 --> 00:12:36,480
Fantastic!

193
00:12:39,350 --> 00:12:41,019
- Well done.
- Thank you so much.

194
00:12:41,019 --> 00:12:42,158
Yes!

195
00:12:42,159 --> 00:12:45,460
My parents always wanted
me to be a doctor

196
00:12:46,129 --> 00:12:48,698
or a stockbroker or something.
They gave me

197
00:12:48,700 --> 00:12:51,969
the first-class education, but
that went all terribly wrong

198
00:12:51,970 --> 00:12:54,399
and I ended up with you lot.

199
00:12:56,669 --> 00:12:59,470
Thank you. I need it
more than you do.

200
00:13:00,370 --> 00:13:02,609
I mean, I have a hot head,

201
00:13:02,610 --> 00:13:04,678
an inability to
tolerate discipline...

202
00:13:04,679 --> 00:13:06,379
- Yes!
- Very true!

203
00:13:06,379 --> 00:13:08,979
I fall out with people
left and right.

204
00:13:08,980 --> 00:13:10,989
The only creatures
I've ever really loved

205
00:13:10,990 --> 00:13:13,480
or treated honorably
are budgerigars.

206
00:13:15,019 --> 00:13:18,229
So in any normal area of
life, I'd be, or I am,

207
00:13:18,230 --> 00:13:19,729
a total liability.

208
00:13:19,730 --> 00:13:22,198
The only thing I've got going
for me is I'm quick in a car.

209
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:24,328
So thank you for this and
for acknowledging that.

210
00:13:24,330 --> 00:13:26,198
I'm going to give
it to my father

211
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:27,668
and tell him to put
it on the mantelpiece

212
00:13:27,669 --> 00:13:30,600
and imagine it's a first-class
degree in medicine.

213
00:13:45,049 --> 00:13:47,019
Well done, Superstar.

214
00:13:47,019 --> 00:13:48,359
Another season like that,

215
00:13:48,360 --> 00:13:49,759
I'll move you up
to the big time.

216
00:13:49,759 --> 00:13:51,528
Come on, you don't
think I'm ready now?

217
00:13:51,529 --> 00:13:52,759
You are.

218
00:13:52,759 --> 00:13:55,099
I'm not. I've got to
find you a car first.

219
00:13:55,100 --> 00:13:56,698
Well, go on, then.

220
00:13:56,700 --> 00:13:58,399
Chop chop. Don't wait too long.

221
00:13:58,399 --> 00:14:00,099
You don't want him to
do what Lauda just did.

222
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:03,038
- Why? What did he do?
- Got himself a drive, with BRM.

223
00:14:03,039 --> 00:14:05,139
How the hell did he do that?
He's a nobody.

224
00:14:05,139 --> 00:14:06,509
He's never won a bloody thing.

225
00:14:06,509 --> 00:14:08,609
Apparently, took out a
Loan and bought his way in

226
00:14:08,610 --> 00:14:10,479
with two million
Austrian shillings.

227
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:11,639
Jesus.

228
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:32,099
Niki Lauda.

229
00:14:32,100 --> 00:14:34,659
Here for pre-season testing.
BRM?

230
00:14:35,639 --> 00:14:38,940
Sign the release form. I'll
let them know you're here.

231
00:14:50,250 --> 00:14:52,019
- Mr. Stanley.
- Good morning.

232
00:14:52,019 --> 00:14:53,950
- Good morning.
- Clay!

233
00:14:54,659 --> 00:14:57,619
Let me introduce you to
our number one driver.

234
00:14:57,620 --> 00:14:59,389
Clay Regazzoni.

235
00:15:00,990 --> 00:15:02,990
- How are you?
- Good.

236
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:04,469
Pleasure.

237
00:15:04,470 --> 00:15:07,028
And these are your mechanics.

238
00:15:07,029 --> 00:15:09,559
They're reporting
exclusively to you,

239
00:15:10,039 --> 00:15:11,509
as per contract.

240
00:15:11,509 --> 00:15:12,609
Pleasure.

241
00:15:12,610 --> 00:15:15,039
- Do you wanna see the car')
- Sure.

242
00:15:16,779 --> 00:15:17,740
Hello.

243
00:15:23,279 --> 00:15:25,580
There she is. P160.

