00:15:26,419 --> 00:15:29,879
- Same as Regazzoni's?
- Identical in every detail.

245
00:15:30,190 --> 00:15:31,989
How much does she weigh?

246
00:15:31,990 --> 00:15:34,558
- 600 kilos.
- But that's crazy.

247
00:15:34,559 --> 00:15:37,259
- Why so heavy?
- It's a V12 engine.

248
00:15:37,259 --> 00:15:40,328
That lump weighs
190K on its own.

249
00:15:40,330 --> 00:15:41,299
Okay.

250
00:15:42,340 --> 00:15:44,969
What horsepower are you getting?

251
00:15:44,970 --> 00:15:47,568
- No, no, 450.
- It's not enough.

252
00:15:47,570 --> 00:15:49,009
It needs to be 500.

253
00:15:49,009 --> 00:15:50,639
And the engine needs to be.

254
00:15:50,639 --> 00:15:52,479
- We already tried.
- Tried what?

255
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:53,479
Everything

256
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:54,979
We replaced the entire
exhaust system.

257
00:15:54,980 --> 00:15:58,580
- Barely made the difference.
- Are you using magnesium parts?

258
00:16:11,429 --> 00:16:12,729
Now the engine block.

259
00:16:12,730 --> 00:16:15,668
Any mounting or fixing
plates, strip it out also.

260
00:16:15,669 --> 00:16:17,099
When you've done that,

261
00:16:17,100 --> 00:16:19,038
we have to look at
the aerodynamics,

262
00:16:19,039 --> 00:16:20,730
front and rear wing.

263
00:16:37,929 --> 00:16:40,289
Okay, thank you. Good night.

264
00:17:00,309 --> 00:17:02,580
What was Regazzoni's time?

265
00:17:03,450 --> 00:17:05,189
1:53.

266
00:17:05,190 --> 00:17:08,489
Okay, now put him in my car and
he'll go 2 seconds faster.

267
00:17:08,490 --> 00:17:11,460
- Well, that's impossible.
- No chance.

268
00:17:13,730 --> 00:17:16,598
We've been working
on it all night.

269
00:17:16,599 --> 00:17:19,068
Put Regazzoni in the car.
See what happens.

270
00:17:19,069 --> 00:17:20,528
I don't understand. Why
am I supposed to do this?

271
00:17:20,529 --> 00:17:21,538
I don't know, Clay.

272
00:17:21,539 --> 00:17:24,029
He wants you to
take it for a spin.

273
00:17:25,210 --> 00:17:26,430
Gloves, please.

274
00:18:12,190 --> 00:18:15,019
- I'd say we push it...
- All right.

275
00:18:15,019 --> 00:18:17,288
What did you do to the car?

276
00:18:17,289 --> 00:18:19,128
That's information
I'll share with you

277
00:18:19,130 --> 00:18:21,088
under certain conditions only.

278
00:18:21,089 --> 00:18:22,119
Go on.

279
00:18:23,329 --> 00:18:25,368
A guaranteed place in the team.

280
00:18:25,369 --> 00:18:27,068
And a paid contract
on equal terms

281
00:18:27,069 --> 00:18:29,368
with Regazzoni for two years.

282
00:18:29,369 --> 00:18:30,898
Are you crazy?

283
00:18:30,900 --> 00:18:33,269
Clay's a senior figure in F1.

284
00:18:33,269 --> 00:18:34,939
You're just a rookie!

285
00:18:34,940 --> 00:18:37,608
The only reason we took you on
is because you're paying us.

286
00:18:37,609 --> 00:18:39,979
Well, as of now, if
you want me to stay,

287
00:18:39,980 --> 00:18:42,479
we rip up the contract,
I don't pay you a cent.

288
00:18:42,480 --> 00:18:44,318
That's outrageous!

289
00:18:44,319 --> 00:18:46,579
Was he quicker in my car?

290
00:18:47,049 --> 00:18:49,019
He was, wasn't he?

291
00:18:49,589 --> 00:18:52,109
Did he go two seconds faster?

292
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:56,890
Two point three.

293
00:18:59,700 --> 00:19:02,169
So, have a think,

294
00:19:02,170 --> 00:19:05,299
work out your priorities
and get back to me.

295
00:19:19,690 --> 00:19:20,650
Hey, Niki.

296
00:19:23,390 --> 00:19:26,588
I know what you're going to say,
that it's none of my business.

297
00:19:26,589 --> 00:19:27,559
What?

298
00:19:28,930 --> 00:19:32,329
If it's the track manager you're
taking on your date tonight.

299
00:19:33,269 --> 00:19:35,038
It's none of your business.

300
00:19:35,039 --> 00:19:37,269
Okay, but if you want my advice,

301
00:19:37,269 --> 00:19:39,069
I'd let this one go.

302
00:19:39,970 --> 00:19:43,200
I'm not questioning your taste.
She is a great girl, but...

303
00:19:45,250 --> 00:19:47,409
Agnes' last boyfriend

304
00:19:47,410 --> 00:19:49,578
was a British Formula 2 driver

305
00:19:49,579 --> 00:19:51,989
who has a reputation
for two things,

306
00:19:51,990 --> 00:19:54,548
for being a little
crazy on the track...

307
00:19:54,549 --> 00:19:57,288
and for going all
night and all day

308
00:19:57,289 --> 00:19:59,989
and all night again in bed.
He's a good driver,

309
00:19:59,990 --> 00:20:02,358
but an immortal fuck apparently.

310
00:20:02,359 --> 00:20:04,298
I don't know about you,
but that's not an act

311
00:20:04,299 --> 00:20:06,319
I'd like to follow.

312
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:11,099
But if that doesn't
bother you...

313
00:20:12,509 --> 00:20:15,200
What's his name, the driver?

314
00:20:16,109 --> 00:20:17,910
Hunt. James Hunt.

315
00:20:21,480 --> 00:20:23,979
You see, you share information

316
00:20:23,980 --> 00:20:25,980
and I share information.

317
00:20:26,289 --> 00:20:28,619
That's what teammates are for.

318
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:42,299
- Where the hell are we going?
- I promise it'll be worth it.

319
00:20:42,670 --> 00:20:44,439
Just keep them closed.

320
00:20:44,440 --> 00:20:45,630
Wait for it.

321
00:20:46,710 --> 00:20:48,109
Wait for it.

322
00:20:52,049 --> 00:20:53,048
There.

323
00:20:53,049 --> 00:20:54,309
What do you say?

324
00:20:54,609 --> 00:20:56,210
She's Formula 1.

325
00:20:56,480 --> 00:20:58,719
Yes, she is, Superstar.

326
00:20:58,720 --> 00:21:01,659
Your brother and I got together
with the bean counters.

327
00:21:01,660 --> 00:21:03,719
And since the economics
of F1 are not

328
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:06,429
so significantly different
to the economics of F2,

329
00:21:06,430 --> 00:21:09,328
well, we thought if we were
going to be losing money,

330
00:21:09,329 --> 00:21:12,469
we might as well be doing it on
the big roulette table in F1.

331
00:21:12,470 --> 00:21:15,730
You fat, little, inbred beauty.
Come here.

332
00:21:20,109 --> 00:21:23,679
Actually, credit where it's
due, we got the idea from Niki.

333
00:21:23,680 --> 00:21:25,278
- Who?
- Lauda.

334
00:21:25,279 --> 00:21:27,679
Bought his way in
rather than mess about

335
00:21:27,680 --> 00:21:29,078
in the lower divisions.
I thought

336
00:21:29,079 --> 00:21:30,378
"Bloody hell, he's right."

337
00:21:30,380 --> 00:21:32,288
No sponsorship, Superstar.

338
00:21:32,289 --> 00:21:33,648
I hope you approve.

339
00:21:33,650 --> 00:21:37,380
No vulgar logos for
cigarettes or condoms.

340
00:21:38,130 --> 00:21:40,189
Just plain white with the flags.

341
00:21:40,190 --> 00:21:42,250
And racing overalls

342
00:21:43,259 --> 00:21:44,390
which read

343
00:21:44,970 --> 00:21:47,660
"Sex. Breakfast of champions."

344
00:21:50,069 --> 00:21:51,630
So when do we start?

345
00:21:52,970 --> 00:21:55,409
- Soon as you're ready.
- Ready?

346
00:21:55,410 --> 00:21:58,069
I've been waiting for
this my whole life.

347
00:21:58,980 --> 00:22:01,309
VILLAGE OF WATKINS GLEN

348
00:22:09,220 --> 00:22:11,259
<i>When the season started,
people wondered</i>

349
00:22:11,259 --> 00:22:13,128
<i>whether Lord Hesketh
and his team</i>

350
00:22:13,130 --> 00:22:15,528
<i>of upper-class enthusiasts
were bringing glamour</i>

351
00:22:15,529 --> 00:22:18,329
<i>to the racing community
or just comedy.</i>

352
00:22:18,670 --> 00:22:21,068
<i>Certainly it was the first
time anyone had seen</i>

353
00:22:21,069 --> 00:22:24,200
<i>a Butler sewing oysters
and caviar in the pits.</i>

354
00:22:24,470 --> 00:22:27,368
<i>But they have made
quite an impact.</i>

355
00:22:27,369 --> 00:22:30,979
<i>6th in France, 4th in
Britain and 3rd in Holland.</i>

356
00:22:30,980 --> 00:22:34,108
<i>All drivers on the track,
caution flags are out.</i>

357
00:22:34,109 --> 00:22:36,648
<i>A severe crash at the Esses.</i>

358
00:22:36,650 --> 00:22:39,088
<i>Red flag. There's a
car off the track.</i>

359
00:22:39,089 --> 00:22:41,088
<i>And reports are reaching
me that there's been</i>

360
00:22:41,089 --> 00:22:43,318
<i>a serious accident
in qualifying.</i>

361
00:22:43,319 --> 00:22:45,528
<i>The identity of the driver
we don't currently have,</i>

362
00:22:45,529 --> 00:22:48,398
<i>but as you can tell from
all the activity going on</i>

363
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:52,128
<i>towards the track, it was clearly
a grave incident indeed.</i>

364
00:22:52,130 --> 00:22:54,699
<i>We will, of course, have more
information as we get it,</i>

365
00:22:54,700 --> 00:22:58,160
<i>but it is the sight and sound
of F1 nobody likes to see.</i>

366
00:23:02,680 --> 00:23:05,170
- Get your hands off me!
- Hey, come on!

367
00:23:14,519 --> 00:23:18,058
<i>Drivers of top stature we've
lost just in the past 4 seasons</i>

368
00:23:18,059 --> 00:23:20,250
<i>have included Piers Courage,</i>

369
00:23:20,529 --> 00:23:21,619
<i>Jochen Rindt,</i>

370
00:23:22,500 --> 00:23:23,690
<i>Jo Siffert,</i>

371
00:23:24,630 --> 00:23:26,098
<i>Roger Williamson</i>

372
00:23:26,099 --> 00:23:28,239
<i>and today, at Watkins Glen,</i>

373
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:31,140
<i>Formula 1 has claimed
another driver.</i>

374
00:23:31,440 --> 00:23:34,169
<i>The Tyrrell team have
withdrawn from the race.</i>

375
00:23:34,170 --> 00:23:36,479
<i>Their places on the grid
will be left empty.</i>

376
00:23:36,480 --> 00:23:39,148
- Terrible.
- They should cancel the race.

377
00:23:39,150 --> 00:23:40,130
Why?

378
00:23:40,650 --> 00:23:43,648
He made a mistake, went
into the corner too fast.

379
00:23:43,650 --> 00:23:45,019
It's his fault.

380
00:23:45,019 --> 00:23:47,249
- Is that right?
- It's obvious.

381
00:23:47,250 --> 00:23:49,318
Look at the tyre marks.

382
00:23:49,319 --> 00:23:52,659
So says the nobody, who had
to pay for his own drive.

383
00:23:52,660 --> 00:23:54,588
How's that working out
for you, by the way?

384
00:23:54,589 --> 00:23:55,690
Fine.

385
00:23:56,160 --> 00:23:58,128
How is it at the back?

386
00:23:58,130 --> 00:24:00,599
Not planning on being
there for long.

387
00:24:01,470 --> 00:24:04,299
Ten minutes to the warm-up lap.
Ten minutes.

388
00:24:07,539 --> 00:24:08,730
Arsehole.

389
00:24:10,440 --> 00:24:13,778
<i>Heading into the Grand Hotel
hairpin, second gear.</i>

390
00:24:13,779 --> 00:24:16,778
<i>Turn in hard, looking
for late apex,</i>

391
00:24:16,779 --> 00:24:18,440
<i>gentle with the bar.</i>

392
00:24:19,250 --> 00:24:21,588
<i>Heading into Portier,
second gear,</i>

393
00:24:21,589 --> 00:24:22,919
<i>clip the apex,</i>

394
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:24,659
<i>light brake, stay in second,</i>

395
00:24:24,660 --> 00:24:26,558
<i>looking for a good exit.</i>

396
00:24:26,559 --> 00:24:28,499
<i>Heading through the
tunnel, gradual right,</i>

397
00:24:28,500 --> 00:24:31,459
<i>up through third,
fourth, fifth...</i>

398
00:24:31,460 --> 00:24:33,299
ls Alexander around?

399
00:24:34,400 --> 00:24:36,059
Yes, he was.

400
00:24:36,599 --> 00:24:38,608
He went back to the
house to take a call.

401
00:24:38,609 --> 00:24:40,308
He'll be back shortly.

402
00:24:40,309 --> 00:24:43,308
He only wanted to show
me his pride and Joy.

403
00:24:43,309 --> 00:24:46,009
Rhymes with 'boy' if you ask me.

404
00:24:46,009 --> 00:24:47,269
And 'toy.'

405
00:24:48,009 --> 00:24:49,719
God, it's so flimsy.

406
00:24:49,720 --> 00:24:52,318
For something that
costs so much.

407
00:24:52,319 --> 00:24:56,019
There's no comfort, no
protection, nothing.

408
00:24:56,359 --> 00:24:59,058
No, it's just a little
coffin, really.

409
00:24:59,059 --> 00:25:01,960
Surrounded by high-octane
fuel in here.

410
00:25:02,259 --> 00:25:04,960
Being driven round 170 mph.

411
00:25:05,269 --> 00:25:08,599
To all intents and purposes,
this thing's a bomb on wheels.

412
00:25:09,440 --> 00:25:11,430
You're James, aren't you?

413
00:25:12,769 --> 00:25:13,740
Yes.

414
00:25:15,180 --> 00:25:17,109
You fit the description.

415
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:18,710
Is that right?

416
00:25:19,750 --> 00:25:22,019
Suzy. Friend of Alex's.

417
00:25:22,019 --> 00:25:23,210
Yeah, yeah.

418
00:25:23,650 --> 00:25:25,279
I know exactly.

419
00:25:26,690 --> 00:25:28,558
What was the description?

420
00:25:28,559 --> 00:25:30,219
Mostly positive in
terms of appearance.

421
00:25:30,220 --> 00:25:32,429
Negative only in
terms of character.

422
00:25:32,430 --> 00:25:34,890
I've been told to avoid you.

423
00:25:35,130 --> 00:25:36,289
By whom?

424
00:25:36,930 --> 00:25:38,199
Alexander.

425
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:40,229
He says you're a bad boy.

426
00:25:40,230 --> 00:25:42,338
Alexander doesn't know
what he's talking about.

427
00:25:42,339 --> 00:25:44,398
I was. I'm not anymore.

428
00:25:44,400 --> 00:25:46,469
The new me is very professional.

429
00:25:46,470 --> 00:25:48,209
Early to bed, early to rise.

430
00:25:48,210 --> 00:25:49,539
All very dull,

431
00:25:49,940 --> 00:25:51,378
but according to the team,

432
00:25:51,380 --> 00:25:54,509
the best way to keep beating
the goose stepper.'

433
00:25:54,509 --> 00:25:56,449
Is that what you were
doing when I came in?

434
00:25:56,450 --> 00:25:59,388
Yes, visualization techniques,
memorising the circuit,

435
00:25:59,390 --> 00:26:02,119
in this case Monaco,
which is up next.

436
00:26:06,990 --> 00:26:09,429
Personally I've always
been a great believer

437
00:26:09,430 --> 00:26:11,358
in getting there on the
day, putting my foot down

438
00:26:11,359 --> 00:26:13,589
and playing chicken
with everyone else.

439
00:26:15,099 --> 00:26:16,669
But they don't want me
doing that anymore.

440
00:26:16,670 --> 00:26:20,299
They want my body like a Temple
and my mind like a monk.

441
00:26:21,140 --> 00:26:23,638
And what about your
soul, your heart?

442
00:26:23,640 --> 00:26:26,039
They've got ideas
about that, too.

443
00:26:26,480 --> 00:26:28,618
They want me to stop
messing around,

444
00:26:28,619 --> 00:26:31,949
settle down, get married with
the next nice girl I meet.

445
00:26:31,950 --> 00:26:34,148
They think that'd
be good for me.

446
00:26:34,150 --> 00:26:35,659
What do you think?

447
00:26:35,660 --> 00:26:37,680
It sounds fucking awful.

448
00:26:40,160 --> 00:26:42,699
But sine they're right
about most things,

449
00:26:42,700 --> 00:26:45,160
they're probably right
about that too.

450
00:26:45,470 --> 00:26:48,400
You don't fancy getting
married, do you?

451
00:27:13,460 --> 00:27:14,430
Suzy.

452
00:27:15,259 --> 00:27:16,990
JUST MARRIED

453
00:27:17,460 --> 00:27:19,460
Hey, hey, hey!

454
00:27:22,900 --> 00:27:25,209
- What's going on with him?
- Nothing. Nothing.

455
00:27:25,210 --> 00:27:27,209
Didn't want to ruin your day.

456
00:27:27,210 --> 00:27:28,329
It's...

457
00:27:28,640 --> 00:27:31,109
- it's the Kraut.
- What about him?

458
00:27:32,180 --> 00:27:34,308
He's just been
signed by Ferrari.

459
00:27:34,309 --> 00:27:36,180
You're kidding me?

460
00:27:36,549 --> 00:27:38,348
Jesus. How did that happen?

461
00:27:38,349 --> 00:27:40,148
Did he buy his way in there too?

462
00:27:40,150 --> 00:27:43,019
Well, the old man
took Regazzoni back

463
00:27:43,019 --> 00:27:45,229
and he insisted
on it apparently.

464
00:27:45,230 --> 00:27:48,420
He says that Niki's a
genius setting up the cars.

465
00:27:55,970 --> 00:27:58,339
FERRARI TEST TRACK
FIORANO, ITALY

466
00:28:06,710 --> 00:28:09,179
It's terrible.
Drives like a pig.

467
00:28:09,180 --> 00:28:12,088
- You can't say that.
- Why not?

468
00:28:12,089 --> 00:28:14,588
- It's a Ferrari!
- It's a shitbox!

469
00:28:14,589 --> 00:28:16,618
It understeers like crazy
and the weight distribution

470
00:28:16,619 --> 00:28:18,088
is a disaster.

471
00:28:18,089 --> 00:28:19,489
It's amazing, all
these facilities

472
00:28:19,490 --> 00:28:21,930
and you make a piece
of crap like this.

473
00:28:52,430 --> 00:28:54,128
"Ferrari family,"

474
00:28:54,130 --> 00:28:55,929
