01:05:49,309 --> 01:05:51,679
<i>In places the track is
still dangerously wet,</i>

980
01:05:51,679 --> 01:05:54,340
<i>but following a drivers meeting,
a decision has been taken.</i>

981
01:06:02,619 --> 01:06:04,489
<i>One minute to go.</i>

982
01:06:14,000 --> 01:06:17,199
Jochen's going on slicks.
You wanna change?

983
01:06:17,639 --> 01:06:19,998
- Is Niki gonna change?
- No.

984
01:06:20,000 --> 01:06:22,340
Then we stay on wets too.

985
01:06:29,710 --> 01:06:32,440
- Niki, okay?
- I'm good.

986
01:06:33,650 --> 01:06:35,880
All right, fire her up.

987
01:06:50,070 --> 01:06:53,268
<i>This season's fight for
the F1 World Championship</i>

988
01:06:53,269 --> 01:06:56,309
<i>has so far been the
story of two men.</i>

989
01:06:56,309 --> 01:07:00,139
<i>Thus far it's been going pretty
much the way of Niki Lauda.</i>

990
01:07:00,139 --> 01:07:02,708
<i>But James Hunt has
qualified fastest here.</i>

991
01:07:02,710 --> 01:07:05,349
<i>He is on pole position for
the German Grand Prix</i>

992
01:07:05,349 --> 01:07:08,610
<i>with Niki Lauda alongside
in the blood-red Ferrari.</i>

993
01:07:10,650 --> 01:07:12,188
<i>It's a long race.</i>

994
01:07:12,190 --> 01:07:14,188
<i>If the track starts to dry out,</i>

995
01:07:14,190 --> 01:07:17,719
<i>the wet-weather tyres will
no longer be as quick.</i>

996
01:07:38,250 --> 01:07:40,119
<i>Niki Lauda and James Hunt,</i>

997
01:07:40,119 --> 01:07:42,219
<i>side by side on the
front of the grid,</i>

998
01:07:42,219 --> 01:07:44,619
<i>go away absolutely as one!</i>

999
01:07:58,670 --> 01:08:00,739
<i>Lauda very aggressive
on Hunt there,</i>

1000
01:08:00,739 --> 01:08:03,369
<i>forcing the McLaren
onto the grass.</i>

1001
01:08:07,139 --> 01:08:10,748
<i>Lauda has the lead right now!
He leads into the first corner!</i>

1002
01:08:10,750 --> 01:08:12,940
<i>Hunt is in second place!</i>

1003
01:08:17,720 --> 01:08:20,088
<i>Mass storming past Hunt!</i>

1004
01:08:20,090 --> 01:08:23,550
<i>He made the right choice to go
with the dry-weather tyres.</i>

1005
01:08:24,329 --> 01:08:26,429
<i>Mass passing Lauda now!</i>

1006
01:08:26,430 --> 01:08:30,469
<i>Jochen Mass, in the number
12 McLaren, takes the lead!</i>

1007
01:08:30,470 --> 01:08:33,198
<i>Jochen Mass, the clear
leader, with everybody else</i>

1008
01:08:33,199 --> 01:08:35,368
<i>making the decision
to change tyres</i>

1009
01:08:35,369 --> 01:08:37,109
<i>after just one lap of this race.</i>

1010
01:08:37,109 --> 01:08:38,970
Come on, let's go!

1011
01:08:47,119 --> 01:08:51,088
See? I told you to go on slicks.
You should've taken my advice.

1012
01:08:51,090 --> 01:08:53,319
Fuck off. Where's Niki?

1013
01:08:53,319 --> 01:08:56,449
Behind you. He made
the same mistake.

1014
01:09:08,310 --> 01:09:09,289
Come on!

1015
01:09:12,739 --> 01:09:15,369
Come on! What's going on?

1016
01:09:15,680 --> 01:09:19,479
<i>The tyre-changing frenzy caused
a huge reshuffling of the pack,</i>

1017
01:09:19,479 --> 01:09:22,319
<i>- with Mass in the lead now.
- You're clear. Go!</i>

1018
01:09:25,159 --> 01:09:27,350
Lauda urging his
mechanics to hurry.

1019
01:09:30,189 --> 01:09:32,960
It's a disaster! Come on!

1020
01:09:43,909 --> 01:09:45,569
What's going on, you assholes?

1021
01:10:09,029 --> 01:10:11,698
<i>This race has gone
wrong for him so far.</i>

1022
01:10:11,699 --> 01:10:13,639
<i>His championship
rival, James Hunt,</i>

1023
01:10:13,640 --> 01:10:15,659
<i>is a long way up the road.</i>

1024
01:10:26,020 --> 01:10:28,349
<i>Lauda passing car after car.
He's just going past.</i>

1025
01:10:28,350 --> 01:10:30,619
<i>Mario Andretti's Lotus there.</i>

1026
01:11:17,569 --> 01:11:18,539
Niki!

1027
01:11:24,340 --> 01:11:25,670
Get me out!

1028
01:11:25,939 --> 01:11:26,909
Help me!

1029
01:11:29,609 --> 01:11:31,519
<i>Several cars are involved.</i>

1030
01:11:31,520 --> 01:11:33,920
<i>Looks like it might be
one of the Ferraris.</i>

1031
01:11:41,060 --> 01:11:43,390
- Come this way!
- Come on, come on!

1032
01:11:55,670 --> 01:11:57,069
Keep trying

1033
01:12:04,250 --> 01:12:06,380
- Come this way.
- Okay.

1034
01:13:44,350 --> 01:13:47,219
<i>The flood, which swept down Big
Thompson Canyon in Colorado,</i>

1035
01:13:47,220 --> 01:13:49,649
<i>was the worst since
records began.</i>

1036
01:13:49,649 --> 01:13:52,418
<i>In Formula 1 today, victory
celebrations were muted</i>

1037
01:13:52,420 --> 01:13:54,628
<i>after a horrific accident
involving world champion.</i>

1038
01:13:54,630 --> 01:13:56,328
<i>Niki Lauda.</i>

1039
01:13:56,329 --> 01:13:58,359
<i>Due to safety concerns
before the race,</i>

1040
01:13:58,359 --> 01:14:00,658
<i>the Austrian had said
he would not take pan,</i>

1041
01:14:00,659 --> 01:14:02,630
<i>but in the end he did.</i>

1042
01:14:03,430 --> 01:14:06,038
<i>He was making up for lost time
when he went off the track,</i>

1043
01:14:06,039 --> 01:14:08,368
<i>puncturing the
Ferrari's fuel tank.</i>

1044
01:14:08,369 --> 01:14:11,338
<i>Brett Lunger was unable to
avoid the flaming wreck</i>

1045
01:14:11,340 --> 01:14:14,279
<i>but was unhurt and joined other
drivers to rescue Lauda,</i>

1046
01:14:14,279 --> 01:14:17,309
<i>who was taken to Manheim
Hospital with severe burns,</i>

1047
01:14:17,310 --> 01:14:20,948
<i>the incident reminding us again
of the dangers of Formula 1.</i>

1048
01:14:20,949 --> 01:14:23,048
<i>Niki Lauda was trapped
for almost a minute</i>

1049
01:14:23,050 --> 01:14:26,109
<i>in a searing inferno
of 800-plus degrees.</i>

1050
01:16:10,229 --> 01:16:15,159
<i>James Hunt gains on the
absent Niki Lauda.</i>

1051
01:16:18,369 --> 01:16:21,270
28th DAY IN HOSPITAL
29th August 1976.

1052
01:19:12,380 --> 01:19:14,738
- Morning, chaps.
- Hey, here's the man.

1053
01:19:14,739 --> 01:19:16,079
Looking good.

1054
01:19:19,649 --> 01:19:22,219
- What's going on?
- Jesus. It's Niki.

1055
01:19:22,220 --> 01:19:24,418
- What about him?
- He's here.

1056
01:19:24,420 --> 01:19:26,340
- What?
- He's racing.

1057
01:19:41,539 --> 01:19:42,510
Niki.

1058
01:19:49,579 --> 01:19:51,210
It's that bad, huh?

1059
01:19:52,279 --> 01:19:53,250
No.

1060
01:19:54,579 --> 01:19:58,118
In hospital, I asked them
straight, no bullshit,

1061
01:19:58,119 --> 01:20:00,958
how bad my appearance would be.

1062
01:20:00,960 --> 01:20:03,958
They said with time
it would be fine.

1063
01:20:03,960 --> 01:20:05,289
But it won't.

1064
01:20:06,399 --> 01:20:09,420
I can tell, seeing
your reaction.

1065
01:20:10,329 --> 01:20:12,198
I'll spend the rest of my life

1066
01:20:12,199 --> 01:20:15,039
with a face that
frightens people.

1067
01:20:17,369 --> 01:20:20,738
You know, Niki, I tried to write
you a letter at the time,

1068
01:20:20,739 --> 01:20:22,229
to apologise.

1069
01:20:22,979 --> 01:20:25,649
The drivers' meeting in
Germany, before the race.

1070
01:20:25,649 --> 01:20:28,519
- I swayed the room.
- Yes, you did.

1071
01:20:28,520 --> 01:20:31,288
That race should never
have gone ahead.

1072
01:20:31,289 --> 01:20:33,079
No, it shouldn't.

1073
01:20:33,189 --> 01:20:37,088
So in many ways I feel
responsible for what happened...

1074
01:20:37,090 --> 01:20:38,359
You were.

1075
01:20:40,159 --> 01:20:41,390
But, trust me,

1076
01:20:43,000 --> 01:20:45,238
watching you win those races,

1077
01:20:45,239 --> 01:20:47,729
while I was fighting
for my life...

1078
01:20:49,310 --> 01:20:52,970
you were equally responsible for
getting me back in the car.

1079
01:21:20,340 --> 01:21:22,960
- How are you feeling, Niki?
- Fine.

1080
01:21:23,470 --> 01:21:24,469
Niki,

1081
01:21:24,470 --> 01:21:28,038
can you confirm to us exactly
which procedures you had

1082
01:21:28,039 --> 01:21:30,048
and the expectations
for you recovery?

1083
01:21:30,050 --> 01:21:31,039
Sure.

1084
01:21:31,350 --> 01:21:33,349
I had a skin graft operation

1085
01:21:33,350 --> 01:21:36,250
where they put half my
right thigh in my face.

1086
01:21:37,659 --> 01:21:39,850
Now, it doesn't look too good,

1087
01:21:40,159 --> 01:21:42,429
but one unexpected advantage is

1088
01:21:42,430 --> 01:21:44,588
it's impossible to perspire
through a skin graft,

1089
01:21:44,590 --> 01:21:46,998
so sweat will never run
into my eyes again,

1090
01:21:47,000 --> 01:21:49,359
which is good for a driver.

1091
01:21:50,430 --> 01:21:52,469
When they heard about
your condition,

1092
01:21:52,470 --> 01:21:55,109
Ferrari immediately hired
a replacement driver,

1093
01:21:55,109 --> 01:21:56,408
Carlos Reutemann.

1094
01:21:56,409 --> 01:21:59,970
Yeah, before ever
reaching the hospital.

1095
01:22:00,439 --> 01:22:03,710
- Is Reutemann driving today too?
- Yes.

1096
01:22:04,180 --> 01:22:06,248
And keen to make an impression.

1097
01:22:06,250 --> 01:22:08,248
So let's see where
Mr. Reutemann finishes

1098
01:22:08,250 --> 01:22:10,579
and where I finish today.

1099
01:22:11,220 --> 01:22:13,219
James Hunt and McLaren
have caught up a lot

1100
01:22:13,220 --> 01:22:15,189
while you were away.

1101
01:22:15,189 --> 01:22:16,159
Yes.

1102
01:22:16,729 --> 01:22:16,890
So is there a question now.

1103
01:22:16,890 --> 01:22:18,529
So is there a question now

1104
01:22:18,529 --> 01:22:21,460
or are you just trying
to piss me off?

1105
01:22:23,100 --> 01:22:25,498
You still think you can win?

1106
01:22:25,500 --> 01:22:27,198
Yes, of course.

1107
01:22:27,199 --> 01:22:28,689
I have the better car.

1108
01:22:29,239 --> 01:22:32,038
And possibly I'm
the better driver.

1109
01:22:32,039 --> 01:22:34,609
But he's a clever guy and
he's used his time well

1110
01:22:34,609 --> 01:22:36,109
while I was lying
half-dead in hospital

1111
01:22:36,109 --> 01:22:37,279
while I was lying
half-dead in hospital

1112
01:22:37,279 --> 01:22:39,109
to win some points.

1113
01:22:40,350 --> 01:22:43,909
And what did your wife say
when she saw your face?

1114
01:22:49,229 --> 01:22:51,020
She said, "Sweetie",

1115
01:22:51,359 --> 01:22:54,420
you don't need a face to drive.
You just need the right foot."

1116
01:22:56,000 --> 01:22:57,399
I'm being serious.

1117
01:22:58,000 --> 01:23:00,738
Do you really think your
marriage can survive

1118
01:23:00,739 --> 01:23:03,229
with the way you look now?

1119
01:23:05,069 --> 01:23:07,130
And I'm being serious too.

1120
01:23:07,779 --> 01:23:09,010
Fuck you.

1121
01:23:09,649 --> 01:23:11,579
Press conference over.

1122
01:23:16,350 --> 01:23:19,618
- That was hairy.
- You know how to get noticed.

1123
01:23:19,619 --> 01:23:21,418
I thought it went
well, to be honest.

1124
01:23:21,420 --> 01:23:23,389
They don't like it when
it's not going their way.

1125
01:23:23,390 --> 01:23:25,029
That's the game.

1126
01:23:25,029 --> 01:23:27,158
- See you.
- See you later.

1127
01:23:27,159 --> 01:23:29,368
- James, are you all right?
- Good, yeah.

1128
01:23:29,369 --> 01:23:32,069
I think I've got something for
you on that last question,

1129
01:23:32,069 --> 01:23:33,368
- about Niki.
- You heard about that?

1130
01:23:33,369 --> 01:23:34,810
- About Niki.
- You heard about that?

1131
01:23:36,270 --> 01:23:37,239
James?

1132
01:23:45,680 --> 01:23:47,409
Please, James...

1133
01:23:47,680 --> 01:23:51,350
Now go home to your wife
and ask her how you look.

1134
01:23:53,760 --> 01:23:54,720
Prick.

1135
01:24:11,539 --> 01:24:14,078
<i>So Niki Lauda, just 42 days</i>

1136
01:24:14,079 --> 01:24:16,679
<i>after his near-fatal
accident at Nüburgring,</i>

1137
01:24:16,680 --> 01:24:18,349
<i>will race here today, at Monza</i>

1138
01:24:18,350 --> 01:24:22,180
<i>against all medical advice and
no doubt in incredible pain.</i>

1139
01:24:26,920 --> 01:24:30,229
<i>Photographers, please,
clear the grid.</i>

1140
01:25:07,630 --> 01:25:09,850
Niki, it's time.

1141
01:25:11,270 --> 01:25:12,520
Okay?

1142
01:25:19,380 --> 01:25:21,310
<i>Please, clear the grid.</i>

1143
01:25:23,479 --> 01:25:25,449
<i>One minute to go.</i>

1144
01:26:11,659 --> 01:26:14,599
<i>The returning Niki Lauda
seems overwhelmed.</i>

1145
01:26:14,600 --> 01:26:17,460
<i>He's been overtaken
by car after car.</i>

1146
01:26:26,609 --> 01:26:29,909
<i>Lauda's off line. He runs
wide onto the grass.</i>

1147
01:26:34,920 --> 01:26:36,988
<i>He wrestles it back
onto the track,</i>

1148
01:26:36,989 --> 01:26:39,279
<i>but that was a bad
moment for Niki.</i>

1149
01:26:43,250 --> 01:26:45,698
<i>Niki Lauda's the
reigning world champion,</i>

1150
01:26:45,699 --> 01:26:48,929
<i>but maybe in his current state
he's a danger out there,</i>

1151
01:26:48,930 --> 01:26:51,989
<i>to himself and to the
rest of the field.</i>

1152
01:26:53,470 --> 01:26:57,569
<i>And Stuck has collided with
Mario Andretti's Lotus!</i>

1153
01:26:57,569 --> 01:27:00,539
<i>Niki's boxed in! He's
got nowhere to go!</i>

1154
01:27:15,289 --> 01:27:17,488
<i>Niki Lauda's actually
making a move.</i>

1155
01:27:17,489 --> 01:27:19,619
<i>He's on Brambilla's tail.</i>

1156
01:27:22,130 --> 01:27:25,269
<i>He pulls out of the
slipstream to overtake.</i>

1157
01:27:25,270 --> 01:27:27,469
<i>Lauda's starting
to find the form</i>

1158
01:27:27,470 --> 01:27:30,300
<i>that early in this race
we believed he'd lost.</i>

1159
01:27:36,350 --> 01:27:39,048
<i>Lauda's now lapping
faster than Reutemann</i>

1160
01:27:39,050 --> 01:27:41,760
<i>and closing the gap ahead.</i>

1161
01:27:44,319 --> 01:27:46,689
<i>Lauda closing on
Carlos Reutemann,</i>

1162
01:27:46,689 --> 01:27:49,059
<i>the man called in to
be his replacement</i>

1163
01:27:49,060 --> 01:27:50,619
<i>in the Ferrari team.</i>

1164
01:27:59,180 --> 01:28:01,338
<i>And there's James
Hunt's McLaren,</i>

1165
01:28:01,340 --> 01:28:04,640
<i>smoking stationary by
the side of the road.</i>

1166
01:28:07,039 --> 01:28:10,340
<i>This is bad news for
Hunt's championship hopes.</i>

1167
01:28:15,020 --> 01:28:16,488
<i>It's Ronnie Peterson</i>

1168
01:28:16,489 --> 01:28:18,868
<i>who comes home the
winner here at Monza.</i>

1169
01:28:18,869 --> 01:28:22,050
<i>But all eyes are on the man who
finishes a brilliant fourth!</i>

1170
01:28:22,560 --> 01:28:24,029
<i>Niki Lauda!</i>

1171
01:29:05,500 --> 01:29:08,038
<i>What a race, what a
man, what a season.</i>

1172
01:29:08,039 --> 01:29:10,208
<i>With a 4th-place finish and
three priceless points,</i>

1173
01:29:10,210 --> 01:29:12,309
<i>Niki Lauda is a
major step closer</i>

1174
01:29:12,310 --> 01:29:15,109
<i>to retaining the
World Championship.</i>

1175
01:30:12,739 --> 01:30:16,509
<i>So the long, grueling and
incredibly dramatic season</i>

1176
01:30:16,510 --> 01:30:19,439
<i>comes down to this
final race in Japan,</i>

1177
01:30:19,439 --> 01:30:21,970
<i>in the shadow of Mount Fuji.</i>

1178
01:30:22,279 --> 01:30:25,408
<i>Niki Lauda goes into this
deciding race at Fuji</i>

1179
01:30:25,409 --> 01:30:27,719
<i>just three points
ahead of James Hunt,</i>

1180
01:30:27,720 --> 01:30:30,719
<i>Hunt knowing he must beat the
Austrian fair and square</i>

1181
01:30:30,720 --> 01:30:32,770
<i>to take the title.</i>

1182
01:30:33,460 --> 01:30:37,059
James, do you think you can
cope with the pressure?

1183
01:30:37,060 --> 01:30:39,429
Well, I've never really
understood what that means.

1184
01:30:39,430 --> 01:30:42,560
I love my job. I love competing.
I love racing.

1185
01:30:43,529 --> 01:30:45,769
Maybe you should ask Niki.
He's the World Champion.

1186
01:30:45,770 --> 01:30:47,399
He's got everything to lose.

1187
01:30:47,399 --> 01:30:49,708
Mr. Lauda, are you
feeling pressure?

1188
01:30:49,710 --> 01:30:52,010
Do I look like I'm
feeling pressure?

1189
01:30:54,079 --> 01:30:55,479
I'm World Champion

1190
01:30:55,479 --> 01:30:58,548
and on the verge to become
World Champion again.

1191
01:30:58,550 --> 01:31:00,979
Hunt now has the
opportunity to win,

1192
01:31:00,979 --> 01:31:02,748
but it's not so easy
to become a champion.

1193
01:31:02,750 --> 01:31:05,479
You have to really believe
it to make it possible.

1194
01:31:05,789 --> 01:31:08,219
James, is there anything
you'd like to add?

1195
01:31:08,220 --> 01:31:10,618
If Niki is being tricky
and getting a kicky

1196
01:31:10,619 --> 01:31:13,010
out of playing mind games,

1197
01:31:13,060 --> 01:31:14,729
then fine, I'm flattered.

1198
01:31:14,729 --> 01:31:18,130
The fact is momentum is with me.
I've never felt better.

1199
01:31:18,500 --> 01:31:20,969
I fully expect the next press
conference we will have

1200
01:31:20,970 --> 01:31:22,600
will be with me as
World Champion.

1201
01:31:27,210 --> 01:31:29,708
<i>Intermittent heavy
rain has been forecast</i>

1202
01:31:29,710 --> 01:31:32,618
<i>here at Fuji today,
along with strong winds</i>

1203
01:31:32,619 --> 01:31:34,179
<i>and occasional fog</i>

1204
01:31:34,180 --> 01:31:36,449
<i>rolling in from the mountain.</i>

1205
01:31:38,220 --> 01:31:40,719
<i>And so with today's Japanese
Grand Prix to come,</i>

1206
01:31:40,720 --> 01:31:43,189
<i>Lauda's lead a
mere three points.</i>

1207
01:31:43,189 --> 01:31:45,059
<i>What a way to finish the season.</i>

1208
01:31:45,060 --> 01:31:46,458
<i>Hunt or Lauda?</i>

1209
01:31:46,460 --> 01:31:50,038
<i>The final chapter will unfold when
we bring you extended coverage...</i>

1210
01:31:50,039 --> 01:31:51,399
They've got to cancel the race.

1211
01:31:51,399 --> 01:31:52,769
It's lethal out there.

1212
01:31:52,770 --> 01:31:54,668
The race is going ahead.

1213
01:31:54,670 --> 01:31:57,168
Television rights have been
sold all around the world.

1214
01:31:57,170 --> 01:31:58,538
The showdown between
you and Niki

1215
01:31:58,539 --> 01:32:00,139
is all anyone wants to see.

1216
01:32:00,140 --> 01:32:03,248
<i>With heavy rain continuing
to fall here at Fuji,</i>

1217
01:32:03,250 --> 01:32:05,509
<i>a decision has
finally been made.</i>

1218
01:32:05,510 --> 01:32:09,359
<i>The 1976 Japanese Grand
Prix will go ahead.</i>

1219
01:32:10,090 --> 01:32:12,680
<i>All drivers to
your cars, please.</i>

1220
01:32:37,109 --> 01:32:39,050
<i>Five minutes to go.</i>

1221
01:33:21,420 --> 01:33:23,158
- All right?
- All right.

1222
01:33:23,159 --> 01:33:25,559
- Hold still.
- What the hell are you doing?

1223
01:33:25,560 --> 01:33:27,229
To let the condensation out.

1224
01:33:27,229 --> 01:33:30,099
- It'll also let the water in.
- Not if you're leading.

1225
01:33:30,100 --> 01:33:33,329
Trust me, this race is
all about the start.

1226
01:33:33,970 --> 01:33:36,600
- Need a hand here?
- Yeah, hold it, Teddy.

1227
01:33:51,319 --> 01:33:53,449
Okay, start the bastard.

1228
01:33:55,659 --> 01:33:57,220
Good luck, kid.

1229
01:33:59,500 --> 01:34:01,119
Good luck, James!

1230
01:34:39,439 --> 01:34:41,399
30 seconds to go.

1231
01:35:01,319 --> 01:35:03,529
<i>Electric tension here at Fuji.</i>

1232
01:35:03,529 --> 01:35:05,998
<i>80,000 bedraggled race fans</i>

1233
01:35:06,000 --> 01:35:09,128
<i>and the racing grudge
match of the decade.</i>

1234
01:35:09,130 --> 01:35:11,368
<i>And there's Mario Andretti
in pole position,</i>

1235
01:35:11,369 --> 01:35:13,430
<i>James Hunt alongside him.</i>

1236
01:35:14,600 --> 01:35:16,738
<i>On row two of the grid,</i>

1237
01:35:16,739 --> 01:35:18,309
<i>there is Niki Lauda,</i>

1238
01:35:18,310 --> 01:35:21,139
<i>and on row three of the grid, Joe
Schecketer from South Africa</i>

1239
01:35:21,140 --> 01:35:22,609
<i>in the six-wheel Tyrrell.</i>

1240
01:35:22,609 --> 01:35:25,640
<i>Behind him, the rest
of the 25-car field.</i>

1241
01:35:42,630 --> 01:35:45,328
<i>There's the flag and finally
the Japanese Grand Prix</i>

1242
01:35:45,329 --> 01:35:47,000
<i>is underway!</i>

1243
01:35:59,350 --> 01:36:01,948
<i>In this conditions it
must be almost impossible</i>

1244
01:36:01,949 --> 01:36:04,649
<i>to drive a 450-horsepower car!</i>

1245
01:36:31,550 --> 01:36:33,719
<i>And it's Andretti
who has the lead,</i>

1246
01:36:33,720 --> 01:36:35,149
<i>but Hunt is attacking.</i>

1247
01:36:35,149 --> 01:36:37,389
<i>Hunt's going round the
outside of Andretti!</i>

1248
01:36:37,390 --> 01:36:39,248
<i>Niki Lauda following
him through!</i>

1249
01:36:39,250 --> 01:36:42,220
<i>Hunt leads into the
first right-hander!</i>

1250
01:37:24,899 --> 01:37:28,069
<i>Hunt comes through to complete
his first lap leading the field.</i>

1251
01:37:28,069 --> 01:37:30,238
<i>At least he has clear
vision in front of him.</i>

1252
01:37:30,239 --> 01:37:33,170
<i>Niki Lauda behind him,
eating his spray.</i>

1253
01:37:52,289 --> 01:37:53,698
<i>Lauda is slowing!</i>

1254
01:37:53,699 --> 01:37:57,560
<i>Niki Lauda is bringing the Ferrari no.
1 into the pit!</i>

1255
01:37:58,229 --> 01:38:01,038
<i>Some sort of problem,
we can't imagine what,</i>

1256
01:38:01,039 --> 01:38:03,000
<i>so early in the race.</i>

1257
01:38:07,710 --> 01:38:09,140
What's wrong with the car?

1258
01:38:09,750 --> 01:38:11,649
What's wrong with the car?

1259
01:38:12,279 --> 01:38:14,418
Niki! What's wrong with the car?

1260
01:38:14,420 --> 01:38:16,649
Nothing. Car's perfect.

1261
01:38:20,989 --> 01:38:22,519
What are you doing?

1262
01:38:22,520 --> 01:38:23,628
I'm stopping

1263
01:38:23,630 --> 01:38:25,689
<i>His mechanics are asking
what the problem is.</i>

1264
01:38:25,689 --> 01:38:28,259
<i>But wait! Niki Lauda's
getting out of the car!</i>

1265
01:38:28,260 --> 01:38:30,029
<i>This is sensational!</i>

1266
01:38:30,029 --> 01:38:32,198
<i>The reigning World
Champion, Niki Lauda,</i>

1267
01:38:32,199 --> 01:38:33,969
<i>is out of this race.</i>

1268
01:38:33,970 --> 01:38:35,439
It's too dangerous.

1269
01:38:35,640 --> 01:38:37,338
Niki, you want me to say

1270
01:38:37,340 --> 01:38:39,908
there was a problem with
the car, for the media?

1271
01:38:39,909 --> 01:38:40,880
No.

1272
01:38:42,010 --> 01:38:43,439
Tell them the truth.

1273
01:38:44,109 --> 01:38:46,009
<i>Now, what is happening?</i>

1274
01:38:46,010 --> 01:38:47,979
<i>They're talking to
the team manager.</i>

1275
01:38:47,979 --> 01:38:50,420
<i>Lauda explaining something.</i>

1276
01:39:05,100 --> 01:39:08,269
<i>With Lauda out, James Hunt
knows he has to finish</i>

1277
01:39:08,270 --> 01:39:12,309
<i>this race in third place or
higher to be World Champion.</i>

1278
01:39:12,310 --> 01:39:15,279
<i>But the job's not done
yet for James Hunt.</i>

1279
01:39:15,279 --> 01:39:17,078
<i>In these dreadful conditions,</i>

1280
01:39:17,079 --> 01:39:19,600
<i>he still has to go the distance.</i>

1281
01:39:20,920 --> 01:39:23,149
<i>Fifteen laps to go here at Fuji.</i>

1282
01:39:23,149 --> 01:39:25,189
<i>James Hunt or Niki Lauda?</i>

1283
01:39:25,189 --> 01:39:28,259
<i>This extraordinary
season is not over yet.</i>

1284
01:39:28,260 --> 01:39:31,590
<i>In this treacherous final
round, can James Hunt hang on?</i>

1285
01:39:32,329 --> 01:39:35,559
<i>And the scoreboard tells a story.
Lap 58.</i>

1286
01:39:35,560 --> 01:39:37,359
<i>Hunt in the lead.</i>

1287
01:39:38,670 --> 01:39:41,260
Oh, God, his tyres,
they're blistering.

1288
01:39:42,170 --> 01:39:46,109
<i>Brambilla very close behind him,
closing on him all the time.</i>

1289
01:39:46,109 --> 01:39:49,439
<i>And he's trying to drive
inside James Hunt.</i>

1290
01:39:49,439 --> 01:39:52,408
<i>Hunt cuts across the
orange March nose.</i>

1291
01:39:52,409 --> 01:39:54,448
<i>Hunt not having that at all.
And he's spinning.</i>

1292
01:39:54,449 --> 01:39:58,219
<i>He missed Hunt but almost took
James Hunt out of the race</i>

1293
01:39:58,220 --> 01:40:00,259
<i>and out of the world
championship.</i>

1294
01:40:00,260 --> 01:40:03,619
<i>Now we find Mario Andretti
closing on James Hunt.</i>

1295
01:40:08,060 --> 01:40:10,229
<i>Mario Andretti's
going past Hunt!</i>

1296
01:40:10,229 --> 01:40:13,359
<i>Hunt is slowing. James Hunt
seems to have a problem.</i>

1297
01:40:18,609 --> 01:40:20,378
<i>Despite this wet conditions,</i>

1298
01:40:20,380 --> 01:40:22,868
<i>these wet-weather tyres
wear extremely fast.</i>

1299
01:40:22,869 --> 01:40:25,029
Hunt's tyres, they're gone.

1300
01:40:25,029 --> 01:40:28,409
<i>Hunt nursing his car
back to the pit stop.</i>

1301
01:40:30,390 --> 01:40:33,359
<i>That back marker's
going past Hunt.</i>

1302
01:40:33,359 --> 01:40:35,720
LAP 70 4 LAPS TO GO

1303
01:40:44,529 --> 01:40:47,998
<i>Look at that left front tyre,
right front tyre, sorry.</i>

1304
01:40:48,000 --> 01:40:51,269
<i>No tread on it at all. And
the other one is flat.</i>

1305
01:40:51,270 --> 01:40:52,739
Let's go! Let's go!

1306
01:40:57,680 --> 01:41:00,349
Okay? When did you
break your gear lever?

1307
01:41:00,350 --> 01:41:02,149
Nine or ten laps ago.

1308
01:41:02,149 --> 01:41:04,519
- Alistair, we need to lift it!
- Come on!

1309
01:41:04,520 --> 01:41:06,259
- At the front!
- Let's go!

1310
01:41:06,260 --> 01:41:09,359
<i>Regazzoni's Ferrari and
Jacques Lafitte in the Ligier</i>

1311
01:41:09,359 --> 01:41:11,088
<i>have gone ahead.</i>

1312
01:41:11,090 --> 01:41:12,489
Come on, hurry!

1313
01:41:13,029 --> 01:41:16,159
You did it. You're going
to be World Champion!

1314
01:41:16,670 --> 01:41:17,689
Not yet.

1315
01:41:17,689 --> 01:41:21,269
<i>A few laps ago, James Hunt was
looking like champion elect.</i>

1316
01:41:21,270 --> 01:41:24,170
<i>Now it looks as though it's
all gone wrong for him.</i>

1317
01:41:25,569 --> 01:41:27,009
- James.
- Come on!

1318
01:41:27,010 --> 01:41:28,139
- Listen.
- What?

1319
01:41:28,140 --> 01:41:30,509
Just go easy out there.

1320
01:41:30,510 --> 01:41:34,418
- What are you saying?
- I'm saying look after yourself.

1321
01:41:34,420 --> 01:41:36,649
We want you back in one piece.

1322
01:41:36,649 --> 01:41:40,019
You're too far back. There's too
many drivers in front of you.

1323
01:41:40,020 --> 01:41:43,420
- There's always next year.
- So that's it? It's over?

1324
01:41:44,430 --> 01:41:45,390
Clear!

1325
01:41:45,989 --> 01:41:46,960
James!

1326
01:41:48,600 --> 01:41:50,590
- Clear!
- Fuck it!

1327
01:41:54,970 --> 01:41:57,769
<i>James Hunt rejoins the
race in sixth position.</i>

1328
01:41:57,770 --> 01:42:02,010
<i>There are four laps to go.
Surely no way back for the Brit.</i>

1329
01:42:21,600 --> 01:42:23,298
Concentrate, Superstar.

1330
01:42:23,300 --> 01:42:25,298
<i>Just brings it back
under control!</i>

1331
01:42:25,300 --> 01:42:28,270
<i>Sliding the McLaren on
the very edge there.</i>

1332
01:42:30,170 --> 01:42:33,038
<i>Hunt's M23 twitching this
way and that under braking.</i>

1333
01:42:33,039 --> 01:42:34,408
<i>And he almost loses
it right there.</i>

1334
01:42:34,409 --> 01:42:36,009
<i>Hunt on the tail
of Jacques Lafitte</i>

1335
01:42:36,010 --> 01:42:37,569
<i>in the blue Ligier.</i>

1336
01:42:45,189 --> 01:42:46,949
Don't do it, James.

1337
01:42:49,460 --> 01:42:51,229
<i>He's inches away
from the pit wall!</i>

1338
01:42:51,229 --> 01:42:53,350
<i>He's inches away
from the Ligier!</i>

1339
01:43:02,300 --> 01:43:04,509
<i>James Hunt has made
up another place,</i>

1340
01:43:04,510 --> 01:43:07,670
<i>but it's not enough and
this race is running out.</i>

1341
01:43:16,119 --> 01:43:19,050
<i>And Watson has spun!
Watson has spun!</i>

1342
01:43:22,390 --> 01:43:25,429
<i>Hunt manages to weave his
way between the back marker</i>

1343
01:43:25,430 --> 01:43:27,698
<i>and the stationary Penske.</i>

1344
01:43:27,699 --> 01:43:30,328
<i>He's catching Regazzoni,
but in these conditions,</i>

1345
01:43:30,329 --> 01:43:33,960
<i>it's one thing to catch up,
quite another to overtake.</i>

1346
01:43:37,109 --> 01:43:39,668
<i>He's alongside Clay Regazzoni!
This could be</i>

1347
01:43:39,670 --> 01:43:41,609
<i>the world championship!</i>

1348
01:43:49,279 --> 01:43:51,010
<i>He's got him!</i>

1349
01:44:06,439 --> 01:44:08,298
<i>Hunt crosses the line.</i>

1350
01:44:08,300 --> 01:44:11,408
<i>He needed to finish third
to score enough points</i>

1351
01:44:11,409 --> 01:44:13,009
<i>to be World Champion,</i>

1352
01:44:13,010 --> 01:44:15,338
<i>and in the confusion
here we're being told</i>

1353
01:44:15,340 --> 01:44:17,078
<i>that he may have finished 5th.</i>

1354
01:44:17,079 --> 01:44:18,210
He finished fifth?

1355
01:44:19,449 --> 01:44:22,048
<i>Our lap charts show
Hunt in third place.</i>

1356
01:44:22,050 --> 01:44:23,918
<i>Well, if the scoreboard's right,</i>

1357
01:44:23,920 --> 01:44:26,559
<i>it means he's just missed
out on the championship.</i>

1358
01:44:26,560 --> 01:44:30,180
<i>Crushing defeat for Hunt
after such a heroic drive.</i>

1359
01:44:34,159 --> 01:44:36,429
<i>I can see the race
stewards conferring,</i>

1360
01:44:36,430 --> 01:44:38,698
<i>examining the
official lap charts.</i>

1361
01:44:38,699 --> 01:44:41,930
<i>We're just going to have to
wait for their verdict here.</i>

1362
01:44:58,590 --> 01:45:00,059
Let's get you out
of here, buddy.

1363
01:45:00,060 --> 01:45:02,319
I'm sorry, Teddy. I thought
I could make up the ground.

1364
01:45:02,319 --> 01:45:04,429
Sony? What are you talking about?
You did it!

1365
01:45:04,430 --> 01:45:07,328
- Did what?
- Jesus! You crazy bastard!

1366
01:45:07,329 --> 01:45:09,969
You came 3rd! You
got the points!

1367
01:45:09,970 --> 01:45:11,599
You're champion of the world!

1368
01:45:11,600 --> 01:45:14,639
<i>James Hunt is now
officially confirmed</i>

1369
01:45:14,640 --> 01:45:17,238
<i>as finishing third
here in Japan,</i>

1370
01:45:17,239 --> 01:45:20,500
<i>and that means he is
champion of the world.</i>

1371
01:45:22,210 --> 01:45:24,908
<i>Our new World
Champion, James Hunt,</i>

1372
01:45:24,909 --> 01:45:27,439
<i>by just one single point.</i>

1373
01:45:33,260 --> 01:45:35,159
<i>Did we really win?</i>

1374
01:45:38,229 --> 01:45:40,390
World bloody Champion!

1375
01:45:49,170 --> 01:45:53,039
- What are you going to do now?
- I shall be getting drunk.

1376
01:45:54,010 --> 01:45:56,479
It's wonderful, absolute dream.

1377
01:46:42,989 --> 01:46:46,628
<i>And our special guest, Formula
1 champion, James Hunt.</i>

1378
01:46:46,630 --> 01:46:49,289
JAMES HUNT WORLD CHAMPION

1379
01:46:59,210 --> 01:47:01,229
JAMES HUNT AGAINST ALL ODDS

1380
01:47:11,090 --> 01:47:13,109
Wait. Come on.

1381
01:47:15,659 --> 01:47:19,020
There's no better motor
oil than Havoline.

1382
01:47:29,899 --> 01:47:33,208
- Yes, me too. Where we going?
- Anywhere I want to go.

1383
01:47:33,210 --> 01:47:35,679
And I don't have to
hijack it, either.

1384
01:47:35,680 --> 01:47:37,948
As long as I pay for it.

1385
01:47:37,949 --> 01:47:40,380
I'm starving. Let's
get some food.

1386
01:47:46,449 --> 01:47:48,449
BOLOGNA, ITALY

1387
01:47:51,060 --> 01:47:53,029
- Where are you going?
- You lot go ahead.

1388
01:47:53,029 --> 01:47:54,930
I won't be a minute.

1389
01:47:56,460 --> 01:47:57,430
Niki!

1390
01:48:00,439 --> 01:48:01,930
Good to see you!

1391
01:48:06,239 --> 01:48:08,208
I heard you were spending
more and more time

1392
01:48:08,210 --> 01:48:10,448
- in one of these.
- Do you fly?

1393
01:48:10,449 --> 01:48:11,448
No.

1394
01:48:11,449 --> 01:48:14,179
- I don't think they'd insure me.
- You should try.

1395
01:48:14,180 --> 01:48:15,418
It's good for discipline.

1396
01:48:15,420 --> 01:48:16,988
You have to stay
within the rules,

1397
01:48:16,989 --> 01:48:18,689
stick to regulation,
suppress the ego.

1398
01:48:18,689 --> 01:48:20,618
It helps with the racing.

1399
01:48:20,619 --> 01:48:23,359
And there I was thinking you
were about to wax lyrical

1400
01:48:23,359 --> 01:48:26,920
- about the romance of flight.
- No, that's all bullshit.

1401
01:48:28,399 --> 01:48:30,269
So what brings you here?

1402
01:48:30,270 --> 01:48:32,029
A friend's wedding.

1403
01:48:32,029 --> 01:48:33,368
At least I think
it was a wedding.

1404
01:48:33,369 --> 01:48:34,599
Might have been a
birthday or something.

1405
01:48:34,600 --> 01:48:36,269
It's all a bit of a blur.

1406
01:48:36,270 --> 01:48:39,168
- Have you been at Fiorano?
- Pre-season testing.

1407
01:48:39,170 --> 01:48:41,139
- You're relentless.
- Thank you.

1408
01:48:41,140 --> 01:48:43,078
I'm not sure that was
meant as a compliment.

1409
01:48:43,079 --> 01:48:45,948
When do you start testing?
Next week?

1410
01:48:45,949 --> 01:48:47,649
No. What, are you nuts?

1411
01:48:47,649 --> 01:48:49,279
I didn't just win the
biggest thing of my life

1412
01:48:49,279 --> 01:48:51,590
so I could get right
back to work.

1413
01:48:51,989 --> 01:48:54,229
Why? You have to.

1414
01:48:54,689 --> 01:48:56,618
To prove to all the people

1415
01:48:56,619 --> 01:48:58,458
who will always say you
just won it because...

1416
01:48:58,460 --> 01:49:01,899
Because of what? Because
of your accident?

1417
01:49:03,029 --> 01:49:05,969
Niki, is that other
people or is that you?

1418
01:49:05,970 --> 01:49:07,368
I won, okay?

1419
01:49:07,369 --> 01:49:09,168
On the all-important day
when it came down to it,

1420
01:49:09,170 --> 01:49:12,109
we raced on equal terms,
equally good cars.

1421
01:49:12,109 --> 01:49:14,338
And I put my life on the
line and I saw it through.

1422
01:49:14,340 --> 01:49:16,378
- And you call that winning?
- Yes.

1423
01:49:16,380 --> 01:49:19,009
The risks were totally
unacceptable.

1424
01:49:19,010 --> 01:49:20,679
You were prepared to die.

1425
01:49:20,680 --> 01:49:23,219
- To me, that's losing.
- Yes, I was. I admit it.

1426
01:49:23,220 --> 01:49:26,048
I was prepared to die
to beat you that day.

1427
01:49:26,050 --> 01:49:28,059
And that's the effect
you have on me.

1428
01:49:28,060 --> 01:49:31,119
You'd pushed me that far.
And it felt great!

1429
01:49:31,630 --> 01:49:34,259
I mean, hell, isn't that
what we're in this for?

1430
01:49:34,260 --> 01:49:37,060
To stare death in the
face and to cheat it?

1431
01:49:37,970 --> 01:49:40,069
Come on, there's
nobility in that.

1432
01:49:40,069 --> 01:49:41,970
It's like being knights.

1433
01:49:42,270 --> 01:49:44,668
You English, you're
such assholes.

1434
01:49:44,670 --> 01:49:46,939
You know my position.

1435
01:49:46,939 --> 01:49:48,179
20% risk.

1436
01:49:48,180 --> 01:49:50,948
No, Niki, don't bring the
percentages into this.

1437
01:49:50,949 --> 01:49:52,408
Don't be a pro.

1438
01:49:52,409 --> 01:49:55,149
The minute you do that, you
kill what's good about this.

1439
01:49:55,149 --> 01:49:56,909
You kill the sport.

1440
01:49:59,949 --> 01:50:00,920
James!

1441
01:50:01,920 --> 01:50:02,909
James!

1442
01:50:06,590 --> 01:50:08,119
I've got to go.

1443
01:50:09,600 --> 01:50:11,659
Careful in this thing.

1444
01:50:12,630 --> 01:50:13,689
James.

1445
01:50:19,310 --> 01:50:22,899
In hospital, the toughest part
of my treatment was the vacuum.

1446
01:50:23,380 --> 01:50:25,448
Pumping the shit
out of my lungs.

1447
01:50:25,449 --> 01:50:26,970
It was hell.

1448
01:50:27,420 --> 01:50:30,019
And while doing it, I was
watching television.

1449
01:50:30,020 --> 01:50:32,948
- You winning all my points.
- Your points?

1450
01:50:32,949 --> 01:50:35,958
"That bastard, Hunt," I'd say.
"I hate that guy."

1451
01:50:35,960 --> 01:50:37,729
And one day, the
doctor came and said,

1452
01:50:37,729 --> 01:50:40,359
"Mr. Lauda, may I offer
a piece of advice?"

1453
01:50:40,359 --> 01:50:42,599
"Stop thinking of it as a
curse to have been given

1454
01:50:42,600 --> 01:50:44,198
an enemy in life."

1455
01:50:44,199 --> 01:50:46,198
"It can be blessing too."

1456
01:50:46,199 --> 01:50:47,769
"A wise man gets more
from his enemies

1457
01:50:47,770 --> 01:50:49,668
than a fool from his friends."

1458
01:50:49,670 --> 01:50:52,439
And you know what? He was right.

1459
01:50:54,340 --> 01:50:55,679
Look at us.

1460
01:50:55,680 --> 01:50:58,378
We were both a pair
of kids when we met.

1461
01:50:58,380 --> 01:51:00,649
Hot-headed jerks in Formula 3.

1462
01:51:00,649 --> 01:51:03,739
Disowned by our families.
Headed nowhere.

1463
01:51:04,420 --> 01:51:07,288
And now we're both
champions of the world.

1464
01:51:07,289 --> 01:51:08,979
It was not bad.

1465
01:51:09,359 --> 01:51:11,389
No, it's not bad.

1466
01:51:11,390 --> 01:51:13,559
So don't let me down now.

1467
01:51:13,560 --> 01:51:15,458
I need you busting my balls.

1468
01:51:15,460 --> 01:51:18,460
- Get back to work.
- I will, Niki, I will.

1469
01:51:19,000 --> 01:51:21,368
But I intend to
enjoy myself first.

1470
01:51:21,369 --> 01:51:23,939
Some of life needs
to be for pleasure.

1471
01:51:23,939 --> 01:51:27,139
What's the point of having a
million cups, medals and planes

1472
01:51:27,140 --> 01:51:29,609
if you don't have any fun?

1473
01:51:30,079 --> 01:51:32,340
How is that winning?

1474
01:51:33,279 --> 01:51:36,149
- James!
- We're gonna leave without you!

1475
01:51:36,149 --> 01:51:37,140
James!

1476
01:51:41,289 --> 01:51:43,449
I'll see you on race day, champ.

1477
01:51:44,489 --> 01:51:45,649
You will...

1478
01:51:46,090 --> 01:51:47,060
champ.

1479
01:51:49,260 --> 01:51:51,469
You look good, Niki.

1480
01:51:51,470 --> 01:51:55,329
The only guy to have burnt his
face and it be an improvement.

1481
01:52:01,239 --> 01:52:03,939
<i>Of course he didn't
listen to me.</i>

1482
01:52:04,210 --> 01:52:07,448
<i>For James, one world
title was enough.</i>

1483
01:52:07,449 --> 01:52:10,439
<i>He had proved what
he needed to prove,</i>

1484
01:52:10,720 --> 01:52:14,279
<i>to himself and anyone
who doubted him.</i>

1485
01:52:15,189 --> 01:52:18,059
<i>And two years later he retired.</i>

1486
01:52:18,060 --> 01:52:21,260
<i>When I saw him next in
London seven years later,</i>

1487
01:52:21,600 --> 01:52:23,698
<i>me as champion again,</i>

1488
01:52:23,699 --> 01:52:25,429
<i>him as broadcaster,</i>

1489
01:52:25,430 --> 01:52:29,340
<i>he was barefoot on a
bicycle, with a flat tyre.</i>

1490
01:52:29,939 --> 01:52:33,069
<i>Still living each
day like his last.</i>

1491
01:52:34,239 --> 01:52:38,079
<i>When I heard he'd died aged
45, of a heart attack,</i>

1492
01:52:38,380 --> 01:52:40,350
<i>I wasn't surprised.</i>

1493
01:52:40,949 --> 01:52:42,970
<i>I was just sad.</i>

1494
01:52:43,479 --> 01:52:46,449
<i>People always think
of us as rivals,</i>

1495
01:52:46,989 --> 01:52:50,189
<i>but he was among the
very few I liked</i>

1496
01:52:51,029 --> 01:52:53,930
<i>and even fewer that I respected.</i>

1497
01:52:57,100 --> 01:53:00,189
<i>He remains the only
person I envied.</i>

